</P>
<P>
   HOLLAND-SUICIDE (Amsterdam, Netherlands) _ In the last two
decades, mercy killings and assisted suicides of terminally ill
patients have been widely tolerated in the Netherlands. But soon
the country is expected to approve a new law that would give it the
most liberal laws on mercy killing and assisted suicide in the
world. The law would affect people ranging from Alzheimer's disease
sufferers to perhaps even terminally ill children as young as 12.
By Suzanne Daley.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Graphic has been sent to NYT graphics clients.)
