<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-20 02:18 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A9201 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s BC-BKN-LAKERSIDE2-RICE-F     06-20 0585
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKERSIDE2-RICE-FIX-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WHAT'S NEXT FOR RICE?
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
(Fixing slug) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ It might be the ultimate irony that Glen Rice
finally became relevant in what might have been his last game as a
Laker.
</P>
<P>
   Rice did everything he was supposed to do as the third member of
the triangle offense, scoring 16 points, hitting all three of his
3-pointers and grabbing six rebounds in the Los Angeles Lakers'
116-111 victory over Indiana before 18,997 at Staples Center.
</P>
<P>
   He even hit two clutch free throws with 1:16 left to give the
Lakers a 112-109 lead they would not relinquish en route to their
NBA championship.
</P>
<P>
   But before Rice could even get drenched in champagne, he was
forced to answer questions about his future. Someone even asked his
son, G'mitri, where he would like dad to play next season.
</P>
<P>
   ``Miami,'' the junior Rice blurted out.
</P>
<P>
   But Father Rice quickly informed everyone, ``He was just born
there.''
</P>
<P>
   Still, there has been plenty of speculation that the
free-agent-to-be Rice might end up in Miami, or even Orlando next
season.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is what it's about. I've endured all the trade rumors and
ups and downs,'' Rice said. ``To win an NBA title, it's been worth
it. Hopefully, I'll be here as well next season.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's all the things I've been through, and winning a
championship helps. I had a great time. I'm happy for the team. We
worked hard together. I feel this team has a lot of great wins
ahead of it.''
</P>
<P>
   But will Rice be around to enjoy those wins? He made $7 million
this season, and becomes a free agent July 1.
</P>
<P>
   A move to Florida makes sense. It's where his wife is from, and
he played for the Heat before being traded to Charlotte five years
ago.
</P>
<P>
   But the Heat can only offer $2.25 million next season because
it's over the salary cap, so Rice is unlikely to end up in Miami.
The Lakers could sign-and-trade Rice, however, if he were to accept
less than a 20 percent raise, and the Heat were willing to part
with a high-salary player like Jamal Mashburn or P.J. Brown.
</P>
<P>
   But Orlando is a different story if the Magic is unable to land
Tim Duncan, Grant Hill or Tracy McGrady.
</P>
<P>
   ``We'll have to see what happens,'' Rice said.
</P>
<P>
   No decisions were being made Monday night, though, and Rice was
enjoying every moment of his first NBA title.
</P>
<P>
   There was no sign of dissatisfaction that culminated in
Indianapolis when his wife publicly criticized coach Phil Jackson
over Rice's inconsistent role with the Lakers.
</P>
<P>
   Rice was even willing to dole out some compliments to Jackson,
who implemented an offense (the triangle) that is ill-suited for a
spot-up shooter like Rice, because he never gets screens for an
open look at the basket.
</P>
<P>
   ``You've got to give Phil Jackson a lot of credit,'' Rice said.
``He enforced things. Everyone was ready to accept when he
wanted.''
</P>
<P>
   Rice seemed to take matters into his own hands in Game 6,
scoring seven quick points in the first quarter and going 3 for 3
on his 3-pointers.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm greedy when it comes to being involved in the offense,''
Rice said. ``I got it going tonight. I got into the flow. I had
open shots and I took them.''
</P>
<P>
   It was a perfect world for Rice and the Lakers. They both earned
an NBA title, and Rice made the contribution he has yearned for
most of the season. In other words, it was no place for complaints.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was definitely worth it,'' Rice said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
