r f BC-AUTO-INSPECTIONS-HNS &LR;      06-20 0539
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-AUTO-INSPECTIONS-HNS </SLUG>
  
 &HT;     SATURN, eBAY OFFER CAR INSPECTION DEAL  
 &HT;     (ATTN: Ind., Texas, Tenn.)  
 &HT;     (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 &HT;     By G. CHAMBERS WILLIAMS III  
 &HT;     c.2000 San Antonio Express-News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Want to get an honest detailed inspection of your used car to
share with potential buyers, just in case you want to sell it
yourself through the newspaper want ads or through an on-line
auction site such as eBay?
</P>
<P>
   Saturn, that little General Motors car company that has built
its reputation on honest dealing, plans to offer such inspections
through its nationwide dealer network.
</P>
<P>
   Although Saturn worked out the program with eBay, people who
want to have the inspections made don't have to advertise their
vehicles on eBay to avail themselves of the service.
</P>
<P>
   In theory, Saturn said, the program gives eBay a way of
increasing sales on its used-car site by giving potential buyers
more information about the vehicles for sale, information backed by
the Saturn name.
</P>
<P>
   But there is an ulterior motive for Saturn: the company's
dealers will have face-to-face contact with a whole new cadre of
potential customers, people who are planning to sell their cars and
might be in the market for a new one.
</P>
<P>
   The advantages to sellers and buyers of used cars could be
extended to any sales venue. The biggest question in any potential
used-car purchase is the condition of the vehicle, and for years
consumer publications have urged buyers to pay for an independent
inspection of any used car before plopping down good money for it.
</P>
<P>
   For about $100, a Saturn dealer would do a 135-point inspection
of a seller's vehicle, regardless of make or model. The inspection
report can be linked with the vehicle's auction information on
eBay, if the seller wants. If so, Saturn will do it for them. If
not, the report goes to the seller, who can burn or bury it, or
pass it along to a potential buyer.
</P>
<P>
   Saturn dealerships in Houston, Indianapolis and Nashville,
Tenn., will be the first to offer the service, starting later this
summer, and Saturn plans to expand the program to all of its 433
dealers by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
   The inspection reports won't include any guarantee or promise of
a vehicle's future reliability, Saturn officials said. It merely
will list any problems found.
</P>
<P>
   EBay is among several Internet companies vying for a significant
share of the $360 billion U.S. used-car market, which is far less
regulated than the new-car industry. It's a big market, too: 40
million used vehicles traded hands last year, while 16.9 million
new vehicles were sold in the United States.
</P>
<P>
   Of course, many independent repair facilities and some auto
dealerships already perform so-called pre-buy inspections on
virtually any car, so if you're buying or selling a car before the
Saturn program kicks in here, you still have other places to get
the vehicle checked out.
</P>
<P>
   The advantage of having a Saturn dealer perform the inspection
is the knowledge such an inspection will be conducted under an
honest and reliable program backed by a major manufacturer.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Contact G. Chambers Williams III by telephone at 210-250-3236
or by e-mail chambers(at)express-news.net)
</P>
</TEXT>
