<HEADLINE>
GOLF-CART BATTLE CONTINUES
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: Which pro golfers were on the committee that voted to
continue the legal fight against Casey Martin?
</P>
<P>
   _ G.D., via the Internet
</P>
<P>
   A: The nine-member PGA Tour Policy Board, which voted in late
May to petition the Supreme Court about Martin's court-mandated
golf cart, includes four players: John Cook, Mike Hulbert, Davis
Love III and Hal Sutton.
</P>
<P>
   In March, the 9th Circuit Court in San Francisco upheld a 1998
Oregon court's decision to allow Martin to ride a cart in PGA Tour
events. The 28-year-old golfer, a college teammate of Tiger Woods
at Stanford, has a degenerative circulatory disease in his right
leg that makes walking extremely painful.
</P>
<P>
   Martin, a PGA Tour rookie this year, has made the cut in 7 of 13
events through mid-June, including a 17th-place finish in the
Touchstone Energy Tucson Open.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Jennifer Lien left ``Star Trek: Voyager'' and returned this
year for one episode. Did she do any other projects in between?
</P>
<P>
   _ A.D., Woonsocket, R.I.
</P>
<P>
   A: The biggest role for Lien after leaving ``Voyager'' was
playing Edward Norton's sister in the 1998 film ``American History
X.''
</P>
<P>
   Lien, 25, also appeared in the film ``S.L.C. Punk!'' last year
and did voice work for ``Lion King II: Simba's Pride'' and the
animated TV series ``Men in Black.''
</P>
<P>
   Fans can write to Lien in care of Abrams Artist and Associates,
9200 Sunset Blvd., No. 1130, Los Angeles, CA 90069.
</P>
<P>
   Q: What is the name and the composer of the theme to the film
``Last of the Mohicans?''
</P>
<P>
   _ G.S., Gardner, Mass.
</P>
<P>
   A: ``Main Title,'' reused several different ways in the 1992
movie, was written by film co-composer Trevor Jones.
</P>
<P>
   Jones, 51, is a South African musician whose credits include
``Mississippi Burning,'' ``Notting Hill,'' ``G.I. Jane,'' ``Bad
Influence'' and more than 40 other films.
</P>
<P>
   The ``Mohicans'' theme appears on two CDs that are currently in
print: the movie's soundtrack and ``'90's Movie Themes'' by New
World Orchestra.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
