<P>
   SMALL-SCHOOLS _ WASHINGTON _ Students in Chicago's new small
public schools are less likely to skip classes or drop out, and may
perform better academically, says a multi-year academic study to be
released and discussed here Tuesday. The findings support Education
Secretary Richard Riley's call to ``stop building high schools the
size of large shopping malls.'' But cost-conscious skeptics remain
unconvinced. Pros and cons of the dispute over how to handle the
upcoming increase of 1.3 million in high school enrollments in this
decade. (Mollison, Cox News Service). 25.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   DATA-SMALL -SCHOOLS on size of U.S. elementary and secondary
schools. (Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   HITECH-RR-XINGS _ BLUE RIDGE, Ga. _ We watch Tuesday as the
federal Department of Transportation and Georgia Tech researchers
field test a possible high-tech solution to railroad crossing
collisions. A transmitter aboard a Georgia Northeastern Railroad
Co. locomotive will beam a signal to antennaes near railroad
crossings that will then relay it to transmitters that can be
carried on vehicles - including school buses - to warn a train is
approaching. Such a device might have prevented the tragic
train-bus collision in Tennga, Tenn., this spring. (Ledford,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   TRUCK-SAFETY _ WASHINGTON _ Sen. Max Cleland, D-Ga., holds a
news conference to discuss a Department of Transportation proposal
that would increase maximum driving time for interstate truck and
bus drivers from 10 hours a day to 12. (Dart, Cox News Service).
18.
</P>
