   TRAVEL
</P>
<P>
   GETAWAY-SOUTH _ From catfish to covered bridges to the King, a
slew of festivals around the South this summer celebrate the varied
and distinctive culture of our region. Whether it's the Lexington
Fire &AMP; Rescue Squad Annual Tractor Pull in Lexington, Ala., or the
World Chicken Festival in London, Ky., there's something for
everyone. The Atlanta-based Southeast Tourism Society, which sifts
through more than 1,000 events each year to find the best fests in
10 Southeastern states has just released its ``Top 20 Events'' for
July, August and September. We provide at-a-glance listings for all
60 events. (Hamilton, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 70.
</P>
