<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ Once again the Supreme Court has
fulfilled its role as guardian of last resort of our constitutional
rights. By ruling that school-sanctioned organized prayer at
football games violates the principle of separation of church and
state, the high bench protected religious minorities from the
public promotion of a specific religion. Gov. George W. Bush,
pandering to the religious right, was disingenuous to claim the
ruling means students cannot pray. Of course they can, but they
can't impose their prayer on others. By MARIANNE MEANS.
