<P>
   VOYEUR NATION: We've become a nation of peeping Toms. We like to
watch, and we especially like to watch real people in dangerous,
pathetic, embarrassing or scandalous situations. We peep into
private homes, island campsites, studio confessionals and any other
place human nature is on display. For many people, reality _ in the
form of births, birthdays, weddings, anniversaries, even funerals _
doesn't exist without video images.
</P>
