</P>
<P>
   SCI-CLIMATE (Undated) _ No colorful foliage in the fall to lure
carloads of leaf peepers. Hardly any skiing. And a coastline
ereoded by violent storms. That could be the New England of 2100,
according to a White House report on climate change. By David L.
Chandler. 1700 words.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-SQUID (Woods Hole, Mass.) _ Scientists come from across the
world to study the squid that spawn off the coast of Woods Hole
every summer. But while the squid may be fertile, it's no match for
the human appetite. Are we eating our way out of future medical
advances? By Joanna Weiss. 1250 words. PHOTO
</P>
<P>
