approved a decisive trade bill with China, a vote in the Senate
remains weeks away, and President Clinton summoned a bipartisan
group of Senate reporters to the White House Tuesday to pressure
Republican leaders to set a date for the vote in the Senate. Unlike
in the House, where supporters hustled for votes right up to the
last minute, backers in the Senate have between 70 to 75 votes in
favor or the measure, enough to win handily and easily defeat a
filibuster. By Eric Schmitt.
