<P>
   MICROSOFT (Washington) _ The trial judge in the Microsoft
antitrust case Tuesday stayed all the restrictions he had imposed
on the company until the Supreme Court decides whether or not to
hear the appeal. Although he had been expected to ask the high
court to consider a direct review, the stay was unexpected. It
apparently reflected his previously stated view that he felt
uncomfortable imposing remedies in the case without a quick review
by a higher court. The move may buy Microsoft several months at
least, since the Supreme Court may not decide whether to take the
case until fall. By Joel Brinkley.
