<P>
   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ When a denomination as large as the Southern
Baptist Convention adopts a retrograde policy of disallowing women
as pastors, matters of faith can ripple out into consequences
beyond the ken of the faithful alone. (Teepen, Cox News Service.)
MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ You'd think George W would have learned from
his daddy's mistake about making promises he can't guarantee he'll
keep. Daddy promised no new taxes. George W says if he's president
our nuclear secrets will be secret again. Some campaign promises
are foolhardy, as the senior Bush found out. (Kleinberg, Cox News
Service.) MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio _ A feisty new squirrel has
moved into my yard _ and she's a she. At least I'm pretty sure. We
haven't talked, nor have I done any impertinent snooping but I've
named her ``Sheena, Queena Madison Street.'' (Schuett, Cox News
Service). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   YOUNG-COLUMN _ (Young, Waco Tribune-Herald)
