<P>
   MICROSOFT _ WASHINGTON _ U.S. District Judget Thomas Penfield
Jackson asked the Supreme Court on Tuesday to accept the Microsoft
antitrust case, bypassing a federal appeals court that has
disagreed with him in the past. Jackson also stayed some of the
restrictions on Microsoft's business practices he had imposed as
part of his June 7 ruling splitting up the company. (Glass).
</P>
