<P>
   SHARP-DRIVING _ The air at the Greenbrier resort in White
Sulphur Springs, W.Va., was heavy and moist. A light shower had
nicely wetted down the course for my tour of the Land Rover Driving
School. Instructor Daphne Green was jubilant, ``Oh the light mist
is perfect, it will make for some most interesting driving.'' I
just didn't know how interesting the driving would be. (Sharp,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). MOVED.
