   (NYT1) JERUSALEM -- June 20, 2000 -- ISRAEL-POLITICS -- Fearing
an upcoming deal with Palestinians, thousands of Israeli settlers
from the West Bank and Gaza came to Jerusalem for a mass protest
Tuesday calling on the government of Ehud Barak not to turn over
any land. Meanwhile, throwing the Israeli political system into
even greater frenzy than usual, the linchpin Shas political party
quit Barak's governing coalition Monday.(Rina Castelnuovo/The New
York Times) *LITE
