weapons official at the Pentagon, signals that the Defense
Department is giving itself more wiggle-room on the question of
whether the proposed missile defense system will work. Gansler says
that even if an upcoming July 7 test flight is a failure, Pentagon
officials might still urge Defense Secretary William Cohen to give
the go-ahead for the construction of the system of inteceptors,
computers, satellites and sensors. By ERIC ROSENBERG. (Already
filed.)
