<HEADLINE>
SENATE ROLLCALL VOTE ON HATE-CRIME LAW 
</HEADLINE>
  (With CONGRESS-HATE-CRIMES) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ Following is the 57-42 roll-call vote by which the
Senate voted on Tuesday to expand a federal hate-crimes law. A
``yes'' was a vote to approve to the measure. Voting ``yes'' were
44 Democrats and 13 Republicans. Voting ``no'' were 1 Democrat and
41 Republicans.
